</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Abe, Y. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Nicholls, J. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Ide, T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Penzes, Zs &amp; Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N." box="[595,819,566,593]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 79" refId="ref47700" refString="Melika, G., Pujade-Villar, J., Abe, Y., Tang, C. - T., Nicholls, J., Wachi, N., Ide, T., Yang, M. - M., Penzes, Zs, Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2010) Palaearctic oak gallwasps galling oaks (Quercus) in the section Cerris: re-appraisal of generic limits, with descriptions of new genera and species (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Zootaxa, 2470 (1), 1 - 79. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2470.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">
Melika 
<emphasis box="[680,729,566,592]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Masuda, H." box="[830,1000,566,592]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="222 - 225" refId="ref46985" refString="Masuda, H. (1972) Life of Japanese gall wasps. Insectarium, 9, 222 - 225." type="journal article" year="1972">Masuda (1972)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Usuba, S." box="[1053,1206,566,593]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref54495" refString="Usuba, S. (1995) Introduction to galls of plants: strange relationships between insects and plants. Yasaka Shobo, Tokyo. [unknown pagination, in Japanese]" type="book" year="1995">Usuba (1995)</bibRefCitation>
(the latter according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[179,318,602,628]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="288 - 295" refId="ref41511" refString="Abe, Y. (2006) Taxonomic status of the genus Trichagalma (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the bisexual generation. In: Ozaki, K., Yukawa, J., Ohgushi, T. &amp; Price, P. W. (Eds.), Galling arthropods and their associates. Springer, Tokyo, pp. 288 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 4 - 431 - 32185 - 3 _ 25" type="book chapter" year="2006">Abe (2006))</bibRefCitation>
also mentioned the alternating generations of this species. The sexual generation was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[151,283,638,664]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="288 - 295" refId="ref41511" refString="Abe, Y. (2006) Taxonomic status of the genus Trichagalma (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the bisexual generation. In: Ozaki, K., Yukawa, J., Ohgushi, T. &amp; Price, P. W. (Eds.), Galling arthropods and their associates. Springer, Tokyo, pp. 288 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 4 - 431 - 32185 - 3 _ 25" type="book chapter" year="2006">Abe (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,350,1061]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,674,700]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks (2).</emphasis>
According to the original description, this species occurs in 
<collectingRegion box="[1021,1131,674,700]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
(northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1247,1313,674,700]" name="Japan" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Japan</collectingCountry>
) on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Q. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[272,366,711,737]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[272,366,711,737]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but it has not been re-collected from this oak species since its description (
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[1226,1339,710,736]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="288 - 295" refId="ref41511" refString="Abe, Y. (2006) Taxonomic status of the genus Trichagalma (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the bisexual generation. In: Ozaki, K., Yukawa, J., Ohgushi, T. &amp; Price, P. W. (Eds.), Galling arthropods and their associates. Springer, Tokyo, pp. 288 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 4 - 431 - 32185 - 3 _ 25" type="book chapter" year="2006">Abe 2006</bibRefCitation>
) (except by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinji, O." box="[187,339,746,772]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref52964" refString="Shinji, O. (1944) Galls and gall insects. Shunyo-do, Tokyo, 580 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1944">Shinji (1944)</bibRefCitation>
; see Remarks 3 below). Later, this gall wasp was found on 
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1170,747,773]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutissima">
<emphasis box="[1015,1170,747,773]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Q. acutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1226,1368,746,773]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[1226,1368,746,773]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Q. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,223,783,809]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cerris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,223,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, neither 
<taxonomicName box="[450,606,783,809]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutissima">
<emphasis box="[450,606,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Q. acutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor 
<taxonomicName box="[660,802,782,809]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[660,802,782,809]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Q. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are found in 
<collectingRegion box="[957,1067,782,808]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kitamura, S. &amp; Murata, G." box="[1084,1378,782,809]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref45803" refString="Kitamura, S. &amp; Murata, G. (1984) Colored illustrations of wood plants of Japan II (revised edition). Hoiku-sha, Osaka, 545 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1984">Kitamura &amp; Murata 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="288 - 295" refId="ref41511" refString="Abe, Y. (2006) Taxonomic status of the genus Trichagalma (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the bisexual generation. In: Ozaki, K., Yukawa, J., Ohgushi, T. &amp; Price, P. W. (Eds.), Galling arthropods and their associates. Springer, Tokyo, pp. 288 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 4 - 431 - 32185 - 3 _ 25" type="book chapter" year="2006">Abe 2006</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, we face two possible scenarios: the host plant originally mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ashmead, W. H." box="[1136,1323,818,844]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="65 - 84" refId="ref42279" refString="Ashmead, W. H. (1904) Description of new Hymenoptera from Japan (I). Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 12 (3), 65 - 84." type="journal article" year="1904">Ashmead (1904)</bibRefCitation>
is erroneous or, as suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakagami, S." box="[416,610,854,881]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="67 - 79" refId="ref52473" refString="Sakagami, S. (1952) Zur Cynipoidenfauna Japan und seiner Nachbarlander (Hymenoptera). Mushi, 24, 67 - 79." type="journal article" year="1952">Sakagami (1952)</bibRefCitation>
, the presence of this gall wasp in 
<collectingRegion box="[988,1098,854,880]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
is questionable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,350,1061]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,356,890,916]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks (3).</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shinji, O." box="[364,514,890,916]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref52964" refString="Shinji, O. (1944) Galls and gall insects. Shunyo-do, Tokyo, 580 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1944">Shinji (1944)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<taxonomicName box="[649,765,891,917]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[649,765,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Q. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the host plant. However, this association is probably erroneous (see Remarks 2 above), so we do not include it in Table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,350,1061]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,962,988]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Biology.</emphasis>
The catkin galls of the sexual generation and the detachable twig galls of the asexual generation both develop on 
<taxonomicName box="[283,439,999,1025]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutissima">
<emphasis box="[283,439,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Q. acutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[494,636,998,1025]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[494,636,998,1025]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Q. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[712,784,999,1025]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cerris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[712,784,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[909,1192,998,1024]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y." box="[1203,1317,998,1024]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="288 - 295" refId="ref41511" refString="Abe, Y. (2006) Taxonomic status of the genus Trichagalma (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae), with description of the bisexual generation. In: Ozaki, K., Yukawa, J., Ohgushi, T. &amp; Price, P. W. (Eds.), Galling arthropods and their associates. Springer, Tokyo, pp. 288 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 4 - 431 - 32185 - 3 _ 25" type="book chapter" year="2006">Abe 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Abe, Y. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Nicholls, J. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Ide, T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Penzes, Zs &amp; Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N." pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 79" refId="ref47700" refString="Melika, G., Pujade-Villar, J., Abe, Y., Tang, C. - T., Nicholls, J., Wachi, N., Ide, T., Yang, M. - M., Penzes, Zs, Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2010) Palaearctic oak gallwasps galling oaks (Quercus) in the section Cerris: re-appraisal of generic limits, with descriptions of new genera and species (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Zootaxa, 2470 (1), 1 - 79. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2470.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">
Melika 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
